about.summary: ShellCheck, a static analysis tool for shell scripts

name: shellcheck
raw_meta_yaml:
{% set name = "shellcheck" %}
{% set version = "0.7.1" %}
{% set native = 'm2w64-' if win else '' %}

package:
  name: {{ name|lower }}
  version: {{ version }}

source:
  - url: https://github.com/koalaman/{{ name }}/archive/v{{ version }}.tar.gz  # [not linux]
    sha256: 50a219bde5c16fc0a40e2e3725b6c192ff589bc8a2569c32b62dcaece0495896  # [not linux]
  - url: https://github.com/koalaman/{{ name }}/releases/download/v{{ version }}/{{ name }}-v{{ version }}.linux.x86_64.tar.xz  # [linux]
    sha256: 64f17152d96d7ec261ad3086ed42d18232fcb65148b44571b564d688269d36c8  # [linux]

build:
  number: 0

  missing_dso_whitelist:
    - /usr/lib/libiconv.2.dylib  # [osx]

requirements:
  build:
    - stack                     # [not linux]
    - {{native}}binutils

  host:
    - gmp  # [osx]

  run:
    - gmp  # [osx]

test:
  commands:
    - shellcheck --version
    - shellcheck || true

about:
  home: https://github.com/koalaman/shellcheck
  license: GPL-3.0
  license_family: GPL
  license_file: LICENSE  # [not linux]
  license_file: LICENSE.txt  # [linux]
  summary: ShellCheck, a static analysis tool for shell scripts

extra:
  recipe-maintainers:
    - dbast
smithy_version:
No azure token. Create a token and
put it in ~/.conda-smithy/azure.token
3.6.15
